.TH DABCTL 1 "2026-04-09" "0.1.0" "DAB Radio Tools"
.SH NAME
dabctl \- receive DAB+ radio via RTL-SDR and decode to PCM audio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dabctl
.B \-C
.I channel
.B \-s
.I sid
.RB [ \-G
.IR percent ]
.RB [ \-\-hardware\-agc ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR ppm ]
.RB [ \-d
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-F ]
.RB [ \-S
.IR dir ]
.RB [ \-\-slide\-base64 ]
.RB [ \-\-silent ]
.RB [ \-\-device\-index
.IR n ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dabctl
receives a DAB+ (Digital Audio Broadcasting) signal from an RTL-SDR dongle,
demodulates the OFDM signal, decodes the FIC (Fast Information Channel) to
discover services, and decodes the selected DAB+ (HE-AAC) audio service,
writing raw PCM audio to stdout.
.PP
This is a direct RTL-SDR \(-> PCM pipeline implemented in a single process:
no intermediate ETI (Ensemble Transport Interface) serialisation takes place,
reducing latency and memory usage.
.PP
Only DAB+ services (HE-AAC audio coding) are supported.
Plain DAB services (MPEG-1 Layer II / MP2) are not decoded.
.PP
When file descriptor 3 is open, DAB metadata (ensemble name, service name,
Dynamic Label, and optionally slideshow images) is written as JSON lines to
that descriptor.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-channel " " \fIchannel\fR
DAB channel to tune to (e.g., 5A, 6C, 11C).
Band III channels (5A\-13F, 174\-240 MHz) are supported.
This option is required.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sid " " \fIsid\fR
Service ID in hexadecimal. Selects the DAB+ audio service to decode.
Both
.B 0xF2F8
and
.B F2F8
forms are accepted.
This option is required.
.TP
.BR \-G ", " \-\-gain " " \fIpercent\fR
Tuner gain as a percentage from 0 to 100.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-hardware\-agc .
If neither
.B \-G
nor
.B \-\-hardware\-agc
is specified, software AGC (SAGC) is used.
.TP
.B \-\-hardware\-agc
Enable the RTL-SDR chip's built-in hardware AGC.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-G .
If neither option is given, software AGC (SAGC) is used by default.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-ppm " " \fIppm\fR
Frequency correction in parts per million.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sync\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout in seconds for OFDM time synchronisation (null symbol detection).
If no DAB signal is detected within this period, the process exits with
status 1.
Default:
.BR 5 .
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-detect\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout in seconds for ensemble detection (FIC decoding).
Default:
.BR 10 .
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-disable\-dyn\-fic
Disable dynamic FIC status messages on stderr.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-slide\-dir " " \fIdir\fR
Save MOT slideshow images (JPEG/PNG) to the specified directory.
The directory is created automatically if it does not exist.
Files are named using the MOT ContentName field, or a generated name if none
is provided.
.TP
.B \-\-slide\-base64
Output slideshow images as base64\-encoded JSON on file descriptor 3.
Each image is written when a complete MOT (Multimedia Object Transfer) object
has been reassembled.
Requires fd 3 to be open.
.TP
.B \-\-silent
Suppress all log output on stderr.
.TP
.BI \-\-device\-index " n"
RTL-SDR device index, for systems with more than one dongle.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.TP
.BI \-\-aac\-decoder " backend"
AAC decoder backend to use.
Accepted values:
.B faad2
(default) or
.BR fdk\-aac .
Only available when the binary is built with the
.B fdk\-aac
Cargo feature.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal termination (Ctrl-C).
.TP
.B 1
No DAB signal found within the sync timeout.
.TP
.B 3
RTL-SDR device initialisation failed.
.TP
.B 4
Invalid channel name.
.TP
.B 5
Failed to start RTL-SDR reader.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B Decode service 0xF2F8 on channel 6C with manual gain:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Software AGC (default, omit \-G and \-\-hardware\-agc):
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 11C \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | aplay \-f S16_LE \-r 48000 \-c 2
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Hardware AGC:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-\-hardware\-agc \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B With JSON metadata on fd 3:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \-\-slide\-base64 3>meta.json \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Save slideshow images while decoding audio:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \-S /tmp/slides \\
  | ffplay \-f s16le \-ar 48000 \-ac 2 \-nodisp \-i \-
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Convert to WAV:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-G 20 \-s 0xF2F8 \\
  | sox \-t raw \-r 48000 \-b 16 \-c 2 \-e signed\-integer \-L \- output.wav
.fi
.RE
.SH JSON METADATA
When file descriptor 3 is open,
.B dabctl
writes DAB metadata as JSON lines (one JSON object per line) to that descriptor.
.PP
.B Ensemble information (written once, when the ensemble label is decoded):
.RS
.nf
{"ensemble":{"label":"My Ensemble","shortLabel":"MyEns","eid":"0x1001"}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Selected service (written once, when the service label is decoded):
.RS
.nf
{"service":{"label":"NRJ","shortLabel":"NRJ","sid":"0xF2F8"}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Dynamic Label Segment — DLS (written each time the text changes):
.RS
.nf
{"dl":"Now playing: Song Title \- Artist"}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Slideshow image (written when a complete MOT object is received):
.RS
.nf
{"slide":{"contentName":"logo.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","data":"base64..."}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Slideshow JSON lines are only emitted when
.B \-\-slide\-base64
is passed.
Open fd 3 with a shell redirect:
.RS
.nf
dabctl \-C 6C \-s 0xF2F8 3>/tmp/meta.json | ...
.fi
.RE
